  <title>Data Security and Identity Management</title>
  <offered>fall-odd</offered>
  <scheduleType>lecture</scheduleType>
  <catalogDescription>
    This course will cover techniques used to protect data from unauthorized access or corruption, and techniques used to identify, authenticate, and authorize individuals or groups to access protected resources. Students will work with open-source tools for cryptography and identity management.
      Cross-listed with SEC415. SEC515 students' grades will additionally depend either on participation in a research seminar project or the score from an approved certification exam (taken during the semester).
  </catalogDescription>
